==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Afar
<hw>A*far"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>a-</ets> (for <ets>on</ets> or <ets>of</ets>) +
<ets>far</ets>.]</ety> <def>At, to, or from a great distance; far away;
-- often used with <xex>from</xex> preceding, or <xex>off</xex>
following; <as>as, he was seen from <ex>afar</ex>; I saw him
<ex>afar</ex> off.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The steep where Fame's proud temple shines <qex>afar</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Beattie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Afeard</ent>⟦br⟧
